Welcome to our website

Here you will find information about our Town and Town Council. The Community section gives details of Ferndown's charities, clubs, leisure facilities, societies, churches, schools, sports and voluntary organisations.

We are delighted to provide this service free of charge so please make sure your organisation is featured with up to date information and send us news of your forthcoming events.

If you would like to give feedback about the site or require any further information please contact our Town Council Office or your local Councillors.

Ferndown Town Council is one of the largest Town Councils in Dorset and includes the main community of Ferndown, plus the distinct communities at Longham, Hampreston, Stapehill West and Tricketts Cross.

There are 17 town councillors who serve for four years.

The Town Council Office and Council Chamber are located in the Barrington Centre in Pennys Walk . Meetings of the Town Council and its Committees are open to the public.
